Brazilian Stock Movers: Braskem, Cia. Siderurgica, Redecard

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-07-28T14:07:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/brazilian-stock-movers-braskem-cia-siderurgica-redecard.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:50 a.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index rose 1.1 percent to 58,917.00.  Braskem SA (BRKM5)  (BRKM5 BS) advanced 1.6 percent to 19.71 reais.
Standard & Poor’s Ratings Services said yesterday that its
ratings on Latin America’s largest petrochemicals producer
aren’t affected by the announced acquisition of polypropylene
plants in the U.S. and Germany from Dow Chemical Co.  Cia. Siderurgica Nacional SA (CSNA3 BS) climbed 1.5 percent
to 16.49 reais.  Brazil ’s third-largest steelmaker said it
boosted its stake in  Usinas Siderurgicas de Minas Gerais SA (USIM5)  to
10.84 percent of the steelmaker’s common shares and 10.20
percent of preferred shares, according to a regulatory filing
yesterday. Usiminas, as Usinas Siderurgicas is known, rose 1.8
percent to 11.23 reais.  Light SA (LIGT3)  (LIGT3 BS) declined 2.1 percent to 28.31 reais.
Brazil’s second-biggest electricity distributor was cut to
“neutral” from “buy” at Banco BTG Pactual SA.  Redecard SA (RDCD3)  (RDCD3 BS) jumped 4.6 percent to 26.14 reais.
Brazil’s second-biggest card-payment processor reported second-
quarter net income of 322.6 million reais ($205.7 million),
according to a regulatory filing yesterday. The result beat the
average forecast of 291.8 million reais from nine analysts
surveyed by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
